# Zorino, Republic of Buryatia

}}
Zorino () is a rural locality (a selo) in Barguzinsky District, Republic of Buryatia, Russia. The population was 68 as of 2010. There are 2 streets.
Geography
Zorino is located 24&nbsp;km southwest of Barguzin (the district's administrative centre) by road. Zhuravlikha is the nearest rural locality.
